FBIS4-27452 "dreas106_i_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 29 May 1994 Cambodia Laos Agrees To Help Curb Log Smuggling Laos Agrees To Help Curb Log Smuggling BK2905144994 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 0500 GMT 29 May 94 BK2905144994 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 0500 GMT 29 May 94 Cambodian BFN [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] Lao Deputy Foreign Minister Souban Srithirat told foreign journalists his ministry has received an official letter from the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] in April asking Laos to cooperate by closing its border passes to block the smuggling of Cambodian logs into or through Laos into Thailand. Souban Srithirat added that the Lao Government has already responded to the RGC's request and that Laos would implement the policy of blocking log smuggling from Cambodia through Laos in all areas bordering Laos and Cambodia, particularly in the Stung Treng-Champassak, Ratanakiri-Attopeu, and areas in Preah Vihear Province bordering Laos. [Passage omitted].
